1. SecureImage plugin for chrooted Wordpress

   - Put font TTF file in blog root directory (e.g., 
     /usr/local/site/chroot/apache/usr/local/apache2/htdocs/bmc/blog)

   - Put ImageMagick "convert" in /usr/local/bin of chroot area

   - Copy all appropriate libs ("ldd convert")

   - Copy /usr/local/share/ghostscript/fonts directory into chroot area

   - Copy /usr/local/lib/ImageMagick/config directory into chroot area

   - Make sure chroot /tmp is globally writable
